<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: I am the one who released the &quot;rideable beasts&quot; info</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Khann">Khann</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:24 a.m. 21/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: I am the one who released the &quot;rideable beasts&quot; info<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/e_ci.cgi?read=82" TARGET=_self>I am the one who released the &quot;rideable beasts&quot; info</A> (Jon)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> Firstly i would like to say to all you

<BR>&gt; SCEPTICS out there who decided i was crazy
<BR>&gt; when i told everybody about the rideable
<BR>&gt; beasts - it's in your face now! I have just
<BR>&gt; received an official statement from EQ (I
<BR>&gt; used to work for Verant for the first 3 beta
<BR>&gt; phases) that....
<BR>&gt; The Horse
<BR>&gt; The Brown Bear
<BR>&gt; and the Great Bat-
<BR>&gt; The horse is availiable to most all
<BR>&gt; character classes and races (some exceptions
<BR>&gt; include Ogres, Trolls, and Gnomes) the Brown
<BR>&gt; bear will be availiable to Shaman's only
<BR>&gt; (note this doesn't include the races listed
<BR>&gt; above) and the Great Bat will be availiable
<BR>&gt; strickly to Dark Elves. We are also
<BR>&gt; currently working on formatting others
<BR>&gt; though these will be all for now. Further
<BR>&gt; details and rules will be released at a
<BR>&gt; later date. We hope to have them up and
<BR>&gt; running soon, and we hope that they enrich
<BR>&gt; game enjoyability for
<BR>&gt; all."<<<<<
<P>&gt; Well i'd like to see what you all have to
<BR>&gt; say now!
<BR>&gt; I have to say i am extremely excited about
<BR>&gt; this and i hope you are too! It may make my
<BR>&gt; 6 hours of play a day i little easier- It'll
<BR>&gt; mean my 18th level erudite wizard may be
<BR>&gt; able to run away a little faster when he
<BR>&gt; accidently picks on something too big! Well
<BR>&gt; i hope to see you all soon and i hope you
<BR>&gt; are as excited about this as i am! Goodbye
<BR>&gt; for now!
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
